Task Description:
-----------------
Create the K8s EKS,further you have to do the deployment of the Nginx application and 
access the application outside the cluster.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Steps:
------
1. Create an Ec2 instance
Name - K8s-task
AMI- ubuntu

2. Install awscli, kubectl, eksctl 

3. create a cluster using eksctl in aws eks service.

cluster name - task-cluster
region - ap-south-1
nodegroup name - linux-N-grp
nodetype - t3.medium
node count - 3
fully managed.

4.Verified cluster creation in aWS console under eks dashboard & in terminal 

commands :
 kubectl get nodes

5. create a manifest file to deploy a nginx application 

image - nginx:latest
replicaset - 3

6. Create a service & ingress manifest.yaml file to connect to the application outside of the cluster.





